# statistics_data_smoke.numos — Phase 6C: drive StatisticsApp past its default tab.
#
# Unlike statistics_smoke.numos (which only opens the app on its default empty "Data"
# tab), this script proves StatisticsApp is INTERACTABLE: it grows the data table and
# switches to the computed "Stats" tab, which runs the 1-Var StatsEngine and renders
# its results — a code path the open-only smoke never reaches.
#
# IMPORTANT LIMITATION (honest scope note): this smoke does NOT type numeric values,
# because digit entry into the table is broken by a pre-existing firmware app-logic
# bug. StatisticsApp detects digits with the range test `code >= NUM_0 && code <= NUM_9`
# (StatisticsApp.cpp:553,642), but the KeyCode enum declares the digits NON-contiguously
# and out of order — NUM_7..NUM_9 (row 3), NUM_4..NUM_6 (row 4), NUM_1..NUM_3 then NUM_0
# last near ENTER (row 5) — so NUM_0 > NUM_9 and that range is always empty
# (KeyCodes.h:68-77). Digit keys are silently ignored, so a value cell cannot be set to
# a nonzero number from a script. (CalculationApp is immune: it uses explicit per-digit
# case labels, CalculationApp.cpp:326-335.) Fixing the range test is a firmware app-logic
# change, out of scope for an emulator-only phase — see the Phase 6D recommendation in
# docs/emulator-sdl2-quickstart.md.
#
# So this smoke exercises the parts that DO work deterministically with mapped keys:
#   * AC (nav mode) appends a fresh row: value 0, freq 1, ++_numRows (StatisticsApp.cpp:631-638).
#   * GRAPH cycles Data -> Stats -> Graph; it is the ONLY key that leaves the Data tab
#     (on Data, LEFT/RIGHT are column nav — the tab-switch guard requires
#     _activeTab != Tab::DATA, StatisticsApp.cpp:521,526). switchTab(STATS) calls
#     recompute() + updateStatsDisplay() (StatisticsApp.cpp:318). The emulator `key graph`
#     token is mapped in scriptNameToKeyCode (NativeHal.cpp, #ifdef NATIVE_SIM,
#     firmware-neutral).
#   * The Stats tab then shows the 1-Var statistics over the default rows (all value 0:
#     Mean/Median/.../Sum = 0, Count n = 2 — recompute() includes rows with value != 0
#     OR index < numRows-1, StatisticsApp.cpp:439). Pure <cmath>/STL StatsEngine: no
#     Giac/CAS, no PSRAM, no LittleFS. Fully deterministic (constructor zero-fills the
#     data: _values[i]=0.0, _freqs[i]=1.0, StatisticsApp.cpp:70-71).
#
# As with every emulator screen the only volatile region is the StatusBar clock
# (HH:MM). This phase makes NO golden claim; the screenshot is a CANDIDATE for human
# review only (a clock mask is added by the human at promotion time, rect 4,6,37,13).
#
# Timing notes (deterministic, step-ms 16):
#   * 200 frames -> splash done, in launcher.
#   * 60 frames  -> Statistics screen load + fade settles after open_app.
#   * one frame per key command (1 command/frame).
#   * 120 frames -> Data->Stats tab switch + StatsEngine recompute settles.
#
# Run:
#   program --headless --deterministic --script tests/emulator/scripts/statistics_data_smoke.numos \
#           --frames 800 --screenshot out/statistics_data_smoke.ppm --quiet
# Exit codes: 0 ok · 2 script/parse error · 3 screenshot write error · 4 assertion failure.

log "statistics_data_smoke: waiting for launcher"
wait 200

# Open Statistics (emulator launchApp id 4 — same id as the launcher's Statistics card).
open_app Statistics
wait 60
assert_app Statistics

# Grow the table by two rows (nav-mode AC appends a row each).
key ac
key ac

# Switch Data -> Stats: GRAPH is the only key that leaves the Data tab, and it triggers
# recompute() + updateStatsDisplay() over the rows.
key graph
wait 120

# Screenshot FIRST so the artifact exists even if a later assertion fails.
screenshot out/statistics_data_smoke.ppm
log "statistics_data_smoke: screenshot captured (Stats tab, 1-Var stats rendered)"

# Still the Statistics app after the in-app tab switch (tab switch does not change g_mode).
assert_app Statistics
log "statistics_data_smoke: assertion passed (Statistics active)"
